1
00:00:03,628 --> 00:00:06,589
(Yukiya) My mother didn't commit suicide.

2
00:00:06,673 --> 00:00:11,177
(Seiichiro) “I am fully responsible for Masayuki’s sins.”

3
00:00:11,886 --> 00:00:15,473
(Yukiya) He killed my mother and stole my wife.

4
00:00:16,349 --> 00:00:20,437
The man who took everything from my life

5
00:00:21,187 --> 00:00:23,690
Destroy Masayuki Ise

6
00:00:31,031 --> 00:00:35,368
 (crow's cry)

7
00:00:35,452 --> 00:00:36,661
 (gunshot)

8
00:00:37,454 --> 00:00:39,456
 (Takahashi and others) Oh!

9
00:00:39,539 --> 00:00:40,373
(Masayuki) No, this is fun.

10
00:00:40,457 --> 00:00:41,875
(Employees) Whoa, whoa...

11
00:00:41,958 --> 00:00:43,126
(Employee) As expected, Masayuki-san

12
00:00:43,209 --> 00:00:44,502
I can't believe it's my first time

13
00:00:44,586 --> 00:00:45,670
- (Masayuki) No... - (Employee) No...

14
00:00:45,754 --> 00:00:47,839
Not me at all.

15
00:00:47,922 --> 00:00:49,382
How did you do it?

16
00:00:49,466 --> 00:00:52,093
No, aim firmly like this⸺

17
00:00:52,177 --> 00:00:53,636
Just pull as hard as you can

18
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:54,763
- (Masayuki) Hehe... - (Employees) Wow!

19
00:00:54,846 --> 00:00:55,930
What does the (employee) chairman say⸺

20
00:00:56,014 --> 00:00:58,016
It's like a management philosophy.

21
00:00:58,099 --> 00:00:58,933
 (Masayuki) Well...

22
00:00:59,017 --> 00:01:01,436
Does it come out strangely?

23
00:01:01,519 --> 00:01:03,897
Haha... That's fun haha...

24
00:01:08,401 --> 00:01:09,402
 (Erika) If this goes out into the world⸺

25
00:01:09,486 --> 00:01:11,321
The Ise family is over

26
00:01:19,871 --> 00:01:22,582
(Erika) We have to do something about it.

27
00:02:18,638 --> 00:02:19,889
(Yukiya) Brother...

28
00:02:25,270 --> 00:02:30,024
There's no place for your heart to rest anymore

29
00:02:31,651 --> 00:02:33,278
Just be scared

30
00:02:34,821 --> 00:02:36,781
To the real hell⸺

31
00:02:38,032 --> 00:02:39,367
welcome

32
00:02:40,076 --> 00:02:42,078
‪♪～

33
00:03:38,176 --> 00:03:40,178
‪～♪

34
00:03:43,223 --> 00:03:46,684
(Erika) In case the Ise Group's performance is affected⸺

35
00:03:46,768 --> 00:03:49,687
The space-related business promoted by our predecessor⸺

36
00:03:49,771 --> 00:03:52,607
I'm thinking of selling the whole company.

37
00:03:54,859 --> 00:03:58,279
Now that an American company is interested⸺

38
00:03:58,363 --> 00:04:01,616
We expect to recover most of the investment amount.

39
00:04:02,617 --> 00:04:07,330
It may be temporary, but I think it will be enough to hedge the risk.

40
00:04:07,914 --> 00:04:11,876
In the end, I will leave it to Masayuki-san's decision⸺

41
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:13,461
What do you think?

42
00:04:13,544 --> 00:04:16,005
(Officer) If that's what you think,

43
00:04:16,089 --> 00:04:17,507
(Officer)...That's right.

44
00:04:17,590 --> 00:04:19,425
(Officer) When the predecessor passed away⸺

45
00:04:19,509 --> 00:04:21,719
I wondered what would happen for a while.

46
00:04:22,512 --> 00:04:24,597
I'm relieved that the vice president is here.

47
00:04:25,390 --> 00:04:26,557
(Officer) Talking to the vice president⸺

48
00:04:26,641 --> 00:04:29,769
I feel like I'm having a discussion with my predecessor.

49
00:04:29,852 --> 00:04:32,271
(Officer)…(laughter)

50
00:04:32,355 --> 00:04:35,191
-(Executive) The Ise Group is safe too-(Erika) Hehe...

51
00:04:35,274 --> 00:04:38,945
I work hard every day, but I'm glad you said that.

52
00:04:39,028 --> 00:04:43,825
I'm sure this is the only way to repay my father-in-law.

53
00:04:48,496 --> 00:04:49,831
(Takahashi) Chairman!

54
00:04:50,331 --> 00:04:52,542
-(Employee) Chairman! -(Takahashi) Chairman!

55
00:04:52,625 --> 00:04:55,586
-(Employee) Chairman! -(Takahashi) Chairman, please come back.

56
00:04:55,670 --> 00:04:57,213
(Employee) Chairman!

57
00:04:57,880 --> 00:05:00,133
-(Employee) Chairman! -(Takahashi) Chairman!

58
00:05:00,925 --> 00:05:02,468
(Employee) Chairman!

59
00:05:03,261 --> 00:05:04,887
(Employee) Chairman!

60
00:05:21,321 --> 00:05:23,364
(Masayuki) What should I do about this...

61
00:05:35,793 --> 00:05:37,420
Takahashi!

62
00:05:39,672 --> 00:05:41,257
Hey Takahashi!

63
00:05:42,967 --> 00:05:44,385
Takahashi!

64
00:05:44,469 --> 00:05:46,262
(noise)

65
00:05:47,847 --> 00:05:49,223
Huh...

66
00:05:49,307 --> 00:05:53,353
Ha... what is it you?

67
00:05:55,772 --> 00:05:57,565
...Why are you here?

68
00:06:00,068 --> 00:06:02,153
This is just right

69
00:06:03,988 --> 00:06:06,199
It's dirty and I don't want to touch it

70
00:06:10,495 --> 00:06:12,538
(Yukiya) I heard everything from my father.

71
00:06:15,041 --> 00:06:16,209
(Masayuki) Huh?

72
00:06:20,671 --> 00:06:22,715
Why did you light the fire? ?

73
00:06:26,386 --> 00:06:28,513
Why did you kill me? ?

74
00:06:32,809 --> 00:06:35,770
No, I don't know.

75
00:06:37,396 --> 00:06:41,317
...Maybe your mother committed suicide?

76
00:06:43,027 --> 00:06:44,612
It doesn't matter to me

77
00:06:46,364 --> 00:06:48,408
Because it doesn't matter to me!

78
00:06:53,413 --> 00:06:54,747
(sound of hitting)

79
00:06:54,831 --> 00:06:58,376
Ah! It hurts haha...

80
00:06:58,459 --> 00:07:02,630
You, don't worry about it, it must have been a long time ago.

81
00:07:02,713 --> 00:07:07,176
Hahahahahaha...

82
00:07:07,260 --> 00:07:12,265
Should I apologize? Yeah? Is that enough?

83
00:07:12,348 --> 00:07:14,434
(Spitting sound) Ha...

84
00:07:14,517 --> 00:07:17,228
Even though there's no proof that I did it.

85
00:07:17,311 --> 00:07:20,565
Ha ha ha ha...

86
00:07:25,194 --> 00:07:27,822
Yes, yes, yes...

87
00:07:27,905 --> 00:07:30,324
I'm sorry

88
00:07:30,408 --> 00:07:31,701
Huh...

89
00:07:32,493 --> 00:07:35,830
What if... what if?

90
00:07:37,081 --> 00:07:39,459
Even if I did it⸺

91
00:07:40,251 --> 00:07:42,503
That was 25 years ago.

92
00:07:43,546 --> 00:07:45,965
The statute of limitations has probably expired by now.

93
00:07:47,216 --> 00:07:48,509
Okay?

94
00:07:49,719 --> 00:07:51,637
I'm a victim too

95
00:07:53,139 --> 00:07:57,059
What's wrong with my father?

96
00:07:59,604 --> 00:08:01,814
it's your mother

97
00:08:09,864 --> 00:08:11,741
It's creepy

98
00:08:13,284 --> 00:08:15,411
“It was set on fire”?

99
00:08:18,956 --> 00:08:20,833
Of course!

100
00:08:29,759 --> 00:08:33,054
I got it. I got it. What?

101
00:08:35,723 --> 00:08:39,644
I'll make you an officer, okay?

102
00:08:40,645 --> 00:08:42,438
So calm down

103
00:08:42,522 --> 00:08:46,192
Huh… hah…

104
00:08:46,275 --> 00:08:49,320
Ha... I'll kill you.

105
00:08:50,571 --> 00:08:52,823
Huh… hah…

106
00:08:52,907 --> 00:08:57,161
Huh… haha…

107
00:08:57,245 --> 00:09:01,999
(Takahashi) Chairman! Which one? chairman!

108
00:09:02,083 --> 00:09:05,670
-(Employee) Chairman! -(Employee) Chairman!

109
00:09:05,753 --> 00:09:07,838
(Erika) Masayuki-san?

110
00:09:08,798 --> 00:09:11,133
Masayuki-san?

111
00:09:11,217 --> 00:09:13,719
Ha ha...

112
00:09:16,138 --> 00:09:18,140
(Masayuki) Hahahahaha...

113
00:09:20,393 --> 00:09:25,439
You're going to get arrested again and go to jail.

114
00:09:27,733 --> 00:09:29,068
Ha…

115
00:09:30,361 --> 00:09:37,118
laughter)

116
00:09:37,827 --> 00:09:41,914
Ha ha ha ha ha...

117
00:09:41,998 --> 00:09:46,043
Ha ha... ha...

118
00:09:46,127 --> 00:09:49,964
Hahahahahaha...

119
00:09:52,258 --> 00:09:54,343
-(Takahashi) Chairman! Chairman - (Employee) Chairman!

120
00:09:54,427 --> 00:09:56,220
(Takahashi) What happened? OK

121
00:09:56,304 --> 00:09:57,513
- (Takahashi) Chairman... - (Employee) Oh!

122
00:09:57,596 --> 00:09:58,556
(Takahashi) Ah...

123
00:10:15,823 --> 00:10:17,283
(Erika) Yeah.

124
00:10:17,366 --> 00:10:18,576
(Masayuki) Yeah

125
00:10:19,660 --> 00:10:22,204
-(Masayuki) Say... -(Erika) Hold on for a moment.

126
00:10:22,288 --> 00:10:23,164
-(Masayuki) Come on... -(Erika) Yes.

127
00:10:23,247 --> 00:10:24,206
Huh...

128
00:10:24,290 --> 00:10:27,668
(Takahashi) I'm sorry, I didn't take my eyes off you.

129
00:10:29,754 --> 00:10:30,755
Ah...

130
00:10:31,672 --> 00:10:33,841
Chairman, I'm sorry.

131
00:10:36,218 --> 00:10:37,720
Excuse me

132
00:10:44,602 --> 00:10:46,520
(sound of door closing)

133
00:10:46,604 --> 00:10:48,272
(Masayuki) That guy is dangerous.

134
00:10:48,898 --> 00:10:50,399
What about reporting?

135
00:10:51,359 --> 00:10:53,361
Well, isn't that the problem?

136
00:10:55,363 --> 00:10:56,822
Those eyes...

137
00:10:59,992 --> 00:11:02,787
Those were not the eyes of someone who could understand the story.

138
00:11:08,084 --> 00:11:10,336
I have to do it before I get hit.

139
00:11:14,507 --> 00:11:16,425
I have to do something

140
00:11:17,551 --> 00:11:19,387
(Sound of door opening) (Kyoko) Masa-kun! ?

141
00:11:19,470 --> 00:11:20,805
(Kyoko) Where did you get injured? Are you okay?

142
00:11:20,888 --> 00:11:22,181
It's okay already

143
00:11:22,264 --> 00:11:24,475
I'll take good care of you.

144
00:11:24,558 --> 00:11:25,559
I have to protect

145
00:11:25,643 --> 00:11:26,519
No, it's okay

146
00:11:26,602 --> 00:11:27,978
-(Kyoko) Can you stand? -(Erika) Mother-in-law will take your place.

147
00:11:28,062 --> 00:11:29,230
(Kyoko) Hmm...

148
00:11:30,648 --> 00:11:32,900
You don't have that qualification.

149
00:11:32,983 --> 00:11:34,193
(Masayuki) Mother...

150
00:11:34,276 --> 00:11:36,404
(Kyoko) For putting Masa-kun through this.

151
00:11:36,487 --> 00:11:38,072
What were you doing?

152
00:11:39,448 --> 00:11:41,325
I think you've misunderstood⸺

153
00:11:41,409 --> 00:11:45,079
Ise Group's work is not your role.

154
00:11:45,162 --> 00:11:49,208
Your role is to be strong as Masa-kun's wife.

155
00:11:50,376 --> 00:11:53,629
...If you don't say it a lot, you won't understand.

156
00:11:53,712 --> 00:11:55,047
(Masayuki) Mom, please stop worrying.

157
00:11:55,131 --> 00:11:57,508
I'm sorry mother-in-law

158
00:11:57,591 --> 00:12:01,095
It was due to my carelessness. I will be more careful from now on.

159
00:12:18,571 --> 00:12:19,655
Ah...

160
00:12:20,656 --> 00:12:22,158
(Kaho) Welcome back

161
00:12:23,617 --> 00:12:24,994
I was awake

162
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:28,581
(Hanaho) Hey... I can't sleep.

163
00:12:31,167 --> 00:12:32,918
You can also put something warm in it.

164
00:12:41,927 --> 00:12:44,513
(Hanaho) Where have you been?

165
00:12:48,267 --> 00:12:49,727
Yukiya-kun

166
00:12:55,107 --> 00:12:57,026
Anywhere is fine, right?

167
00:12:58,319 --> 00:13:00,404
(Hanaho) Yes, but

168
00:13:00,488 --> 00:13:02,490
No matter where or what you do...

169
00:13:04,116 --> 00:13:06,160
It has nothing to do with Hanaho.

170
00:13:07,411 --> 00:13:09,455
(Hanaho) It doesn't matter!

171
00:13:11,749 --> 00:13:15,044
(Hanaho) I am grateful to Yukiya-kun.

172
00:13:15,836 --> 00:13:18,047
It's not about yesterday or today.

173
00:13:18,130 --> 00:13:19,757
a long time ago

174
00:13:21,050 --> 00:13:25,262
Because you always helped me at that house.

175
00:13:25,346 --> 00:13:26,889
that's why…

176
00:13:28,057 --> 00:13:31,519
I want you to stop doing dangerous things.

177
00:13:34,813 --> 00:13:36,148
Why?

178
00:13:37,358 --> 00:13:40,277
It would be more difficult not to hold a grudge.

179
00:13:52,748 --> 00:13:54,833
After I woke up...

180
00:13:57,336 --> 00:13:59,213
I've been thinking about it

181
00:14:01,006 --> 00:14:03,384
I wonder why it happened like this

182
00:14:06,428 --> 00:14:12,101
I'm sure it's just a bunch of misunderstandings and misunderstandings⸺

183
00:14:14,645 --> 00:14:19,441
I'm sure it's not that one is bad.

184
00:14:29,702 --> 00:14:31,036
that…

185
00:14:33,581 --> 00:14:34,623
Are you serious?

186
00:14:39,962 --> 00:14:41,338
It's okay now

187
00:14:43,883 --> 00:14:46,093
Because I'm alive now

188
00:14:48,888 --> 00:14:54,977
And now I can finally be free from that house.

189
00:14:56,687 --> 00:15:01,358
The more time passes, the stronger my feelings become.

190
00:15:03,027 --> 00:15:05,070
I don't want to be involved anymore

191
00:15:07,740 --> 00:15:11,785
I'd be lying if I said I don't hold a grudge.

192
00:15:14,622 --> 00:15:18,500
But I'm glad it turned out like this

193
00:15:21,795 --> 00:15:26,842
I'm thinking of moving on to a new life now

194
00:15:29,053 --> 00:15:30,346
that's why…

195
00:15:31,430 --> 00:15:35,601
I want Yukiya-kun to look forward and live his life properly.

196
00:15:44,401 --> 00:15:45,653
I am⸺

197
00:15:47,738 --> 00:15:49,823
To live properly⸺

198
00:15:52,117 --> 00:15:54,203
I'm going to crush them.

199
00:15:57,289 --> 00:15:58,832
If you don't do that⸺

200
00:16:01,752 --> 00:16:04,088
i can't move on

201
00:16:39,915 --> 00:16:42,459
(Fuyu) When your wife gives you milk⸺

202
00:16:42,543 --> 00:16:45,254
Miyabi-sama seems happy.

203
00:16:46,922 --> 00:16:49,216
Is that how you see it, Fuyu-san?

204
00:16:49,299 --> 00:16:53,095
Yes, your smile is completely different.

205
00:16:56,849 --> 00:16:59,184
(Kyoko) It's about Erika.

206
00:16:59,977 --> 00:17:02,020
Also? Don't worry about it...

207
00:17:02,104 --> 00:17:05,065
I just feel like they're trying to take over my house.

208
00:17:05,607 --> 00:17:07,109
(Masayuki) Take over?

209
00:17:07,192 --> 00:17:08,527
Because⸺

210
00:17:09,486 --> 00:17:13,073
The person sitting over there is the vice president⸺

211
00:17:13,157 --> 00:17:15,492
Can you believe it?

212
00:17:16,869 --> 00:17:20,080
Isn't that what you're aiming for eventually? There

213
00:17:20,164 --> 00:17:23,041
Stop it, there were a lot of things going on.

214
00:17:23,125 --> 00:17:25,669
But when did all of that happen?

215
00:17:27,004 --> 00:17:28,255
Yeah?

216
00:17:31,508 --> 00:17:36,388
Everything happened after that person came, right?

217
00:17:37,931 --> 00:17:40,684
So why do you blame Erika?

218
00:17:40,768 --> 00:17:43,103
Everything that happened up until now is probably his fault.

219
00:17:44,396 --> 00:17:48,400
I think Erika is connected to that guy.

220
00:17:50,277 --> 00:17:51,904
Are you serious?

221
00:17:51,987 --> 00:17:54,782
(Kyoko) I even hire a detective.

222
00:17:54,865 --> 00:17:56,909
Hah... just calm down.

223
00:17:56,992 --> 00:18:00,370
Masa-kun, don't be fooled

224
00:18:01,497 --> 00:18:06,335
I think it was because of him that I married Masa-kun.

225
00:18:11,256 --> 00:18:14,468
The eyes of the god of poverty between similar people

226
00:18:41,036 --> 00:18:42,287
(falling sound)

227
00:19:07,771 --> 00:19:11,692
It's been a while. I came to talk to you.

228
00:19:13,026 --> 00:19:14,695
(Nobuo) What happened all of a sudden?

229
00:19:15,779 --> 00:19:16,947
(Nobuo) Hey Aiba

230
00:19:17,030 --> 00:19:21,952
The other day, what would be a problem if I were to appear in this world?

231
00:19:22,494 --> 00:19:23,871
It's Nobuo-san, right?

232
00:19:31,336 --> 00:19:33,046
What are the requirements?

233
00:19:49,521 --> 00:19:53,984
Who told you this?

234
00:20:05,287 --> 00:20:08,999
It's good to be me, it's good to be this⸺

235
00:20:09,082 --> 00:20:12,544
You're making me feel uncomfortable, Nobuo-san.

236
00:20:13,086 --> 00:20:17,925
It's an important time, but it's difficult.

237
00:20:19,134 --> 00:20:20,844
What on earth do you want?

238
00:20:23,430 --> 00:20:25,849
I will free you from the Ise family.

239
00:20:29,603 --> 00:20:33,023
I don't care what you do to me

240
00:20:34,483 --> 00:20:39,863
As long as I can take revenge on them, that's fine with me.

241
00:20:49,456 --> 00:20:50,499
Huh...

242
00:20:51,416 --> 00:20:55,462
laughter)

243
00:20:59,883 --> 00:21:02,803
No, it was my fault for being so malicious.

244
00:21:03,720 --> 00:21:05,430
I'll be your strength

245
00:21:22,656 --> 00:21:24,574
(Male) What do you mean! ?

246
00:21:25,450 --> 00:21:29,246
No, you haven't been apologizing for a while now.

247
00:21:29,329 --> 00:21:30,580
(Satoshi) Sorry.

248
00:21:30,664 --> 00:21:31,999
(Male) Yeah! ?

249
00:21:32,582 --> 00:21:35,085
No, no... ah... look here.

250
00:21:35,627 --> 00:21:38,672
No, what do you mean by "yes"?

251
00:21:39,172 --> 00:21:41,633
-(Male) Why... -(Satoshi) I'm sorry.

252
00:21:41,717 --> 00:21:42,968
(Male) Huh? Why? Eh...

253
00:21:43,051 --> 00:21:44,511
-(Satoshi) Sorry! -(Male) Huh...

254
00:21:44,594 --> 00:21:46,888
Huh? Why are you angry?

255
00:21:46,972 --> 00:21:48,098
-(Male) Are you listening? - (Satoshi) Oh?

256
00:21:48,181 --> 00:21:49,016
(Male) Huh?

257
00:22:05,657 --> 00:22:10,287
(mobile phone vibrator)

258
00:22:10,912 --> 00:22:11,997
yes

259
00:22:14,833 --> 00:22:17,002
Yeah... I get it

260
00:22:17,085 --> 00:22:20,255
Please continue to monitor the situation.

261
00:22:25,427 --> 00:22:27,971
I wish you were quiet

262
00:22:33,060 --> 00:22:33,977
(Kyoko) Masa-kun

263
00:22:34,394 --> 00:22:35,896
Tell me it's a lie

264
00:22:38,231 --> 00:22:42,861
That woman... That woman seduced me.

265
00:23:12,849 --> 00:23:19,564
(Mobile phone ringtone)

266
00:23:21,274 --> 00:23:22,776
(Erika) Hello

267
00:23:25,070 --> 00:23:26,947
My mother found out

268
00:23:28,240 --> 00:23:29,741
About my father

269
00:23:30,659 --> 00:23:32,911
Of course I said I didn't know.

270
00:23:34,871 --> 00:23:36,748
I didn't believe it

271
00:23:41,461 --> 00:23:43,004
It'll be okay

272
00:23:43,505 --> 00:23:46,925
I'll talk to my mother-in-law tomorrow morning.

273
00:23:56,643 --> 00:24:00,063
I didn't think it could be used this much

274
00:24:01,857 --> 00:24:03,900
Thank you so far

275
00:24:53,867 --> 00:24:55,911
(TV audio: Announcer) Because the north wind is getting stronger⸺

276
00:24:55,994 --> 00:25:00,248
It looks like it's going to be a chilly day in northern areas such as Fukuoka.

277
00:25:00,874 --> 00:25:03,752
There is a possibility of showers in Okinawa...

278
00:25:03,835 --> 00:25:04,669
(noise)

279
00:25:04,753 --> 00:25:08,673
It's safe to have a folding umbrella when you go out.

280
00:25:09,674 --> 00:25:14,262
It's going to be cold again today, so please stay warm.

281
00:25:14,763 --> 00:25:18,141
I have told you about the weather across the country.

282
00:25:18,642 --> 00:25:20,519
(Announcer) Breaking news.

283
00:25:20,602 --> 00:25:23,939
Has many companies under its umbrella, including trading companies and apparel⸺

284
00:25:24,022 --> 00:25:27,317
Chairman of Ise Group, one of Japan's leading companies⸺

285
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:30,320
Suspect Masayuki Ise was arrested

286
00:25:31,488 --> 00:25:37,035
He is suspected of murdering his father, former chairman Seiichiro Ise.

287
00:25:38,203 --> 00:25:41,206
The Metropolitan Police Department is investigating the company's management methods⸺

288
00:25:41,289 --> 00:25:43,667
It appears that there was a conflict between the two.

289
00:25:43,750 --> 00:25:46,836
We are currently investigating the motive in detail.

290
00:25:47,546 --> 00:25:50,757
Suspect Ise denies the charges

291
00:26:05,397 --> 00:26:10,694
I'll never forgive you I'll never forgive you I'll never forgive you...

292
00:26:10,777 --> 00:26:12,946
absolutely…

293
00:26:15,407 --> 00:26:18,410
(Secretary) A lot of reporters have gathered in front of my house...

294
00:26:18,493 --> 00:26:21,413
That's probably the case. Do you have any questions?

295
00:26:21,496 --> 00:26:23,039
Available

296
00:26:23,582 --> 00:26:25,500
(Secretary) Which shoes do you wear?

297
00:26:26,418 --> 00:26:28,586
Any news here?

298
00:26:28,670 --> 00:26:31,756
Earlier, I summarized the main things such as TV and newspapers⸺

299
00:26:31,840 --> 00:26:34,634
I shared it on the vice president's tablet.

300
00:26:34,718 --> 00:26:36,094
thank you

301
00:26:36,177 --> 00:26:39,097
Can you leave me alone so I can take a look?

302
00:26:39,180 --> 00:26:42,017
I'll have a press conference in front of my house at 9 o'clock in 40 minutes.

303
00:26:42,100 --> 00:26:43,560
I understand

304
00:27:12,797 --> 00:27:14,341
(Kyoko) Erika

305
00:27:17,052 --> 00:27:18,762
Erika...

306
00:27:20,388 --> 00:27:22,307
Maybe it's my fault

307
00:27:24,643 --> 00:27:29,189
I was asked to find out about Seiichiro⸺

308
00:27:30,440 --> 00:27:32,442
Give that to Masa-kun...

309
00:27:33,610 --> 00:27:34,944
Mother-in-law?

310
00:27:35,028 --> 00:27:37,739
I didn't mean it like this

311
00:27:59,886 --> 00:28:02,472
(Erika) Mother-in-law, this

312
00:28:03,223 --> 00:28:06,017
This arrived this morning...

313
00:28:09,562 --> 00:28:11,106
All this too⸺

314
00:28:12,357 --> 00:28:14,943
It might be Yukiya's work.

315
00:28:30,375 --> 00:28:35,004
(Erika) This time, my husband is also the chairman of the Ise Group⸺

316
00:28:35,088 --> 00:28:36,923
About Masayuki Ise⸺

317
00:28:37,006 --> 00:28:40,719
We apologize for the inconvenience caused to you⸺

318
00:28:40,802 --> 00:28:43,012
I'm very sorry.

319
00:28:46,099 --> 00:28:50,019
I'm surprised it happened so suddenly.

320
00:28:51,354 --> 00:28:54,065
I believe in the chairman, but⸺

321
00:28:54,149 --> 00:28:56,651
If what happened this time is true, that is⸺

322
00:28:57,610 --> 00:28:59,821
it's not acceptable

323
00:29:00,780 --> 00:29:04,159
We are asking for the truth to be investigated as soon as possible...

324
00:30:06,846 --> 00:30:08,640
Landlord, this is...

325
00:30:13,937 --> 00:30:14,771
this…

326
00:30:14,854 --> 00:30:17,524
(Male) We came here at the request of the Ise family.

327
00:30:17,607 --> 00:30:19,025
(Yukiya) Ise family...

328
00:30:22,987 --> 00:30:25,698
(Male) We came here at the request of the Ise family.

329
00:30:26,616 --> 00:30:27,951
(Yukiya) Ise family...

330
00:31:55,997 --> 00:31:57,498
I'll enjoy having this

331
00:32:27,862 --> 00:32:29,072
delicious

332
00:32:30,239 --> 00:32:31,532
(Reo) Good.

333
00:32:41,459 --> 00:32:42,377
Reo-kun...

334
00:32:42,460 --> 00:32:46,881
Could Marble help us with this?

335
00:32:48,132 --> 00:32:51,636
...However, the funds only last for 3 months⸺

336
00:32:51,719 --> 00:32:54,806
I have to do something in the meantime.

337
00:32:58,601 --> 00:33:00,353
thanks so much

338
00:33:02,188 --> 00:33:06,776
I have never had Yukiya-san to thank me.

339
00:33:06,859 --> 00:33:08,236
I'm not doing anything

340
00:33:12,156 --> 00:33:13,574
Yukiya-san...

341
00:33:19,622 --> 00:33:24,168
The one who stayed by my side without abandoning anyone⸺

342
00:33:24,252 --> 00:33:25,670
This is Yukiya.

343
00:33:29,424 --> 00:33:30,550
And⸺

344
00:33:31,759 --> 00:33:34,971
This is for Yukiya-san⸺

345
00:33:35,054 --> 00:33:37,473
Of course it's an important place⸺

346
00:33:39,392 --> 00:33:41,227
That's not all anymore

347
00:33:46,482 --> 00:33:50,611
For Juna-chan and everyone else⸺

348
00:33:51,696 --> 00:33:53,906
It's an irreplaceable place.

349
00:34:01,289 --> 00:34:02,582
that's why…

350
00:34:06,502 --> 00:34:09,797
Could you please let us work together?

351
00:34:41,162 --> 00:34:44,332
(Erika) You know, I...

352
00:34:44,415 --> 00:34:46,042
Are you pregnant?

353
00:34:46,125 --> 00:34:47,627
Child with Masayuki

354
00:34:47,710 --> 00:34:49,462
There's no way you can crush the Ise family.

355
00:34:49,545 --> 00:34:51,506
Shut up and disappear

356
00:34:51,589 --> 00:34:54,884
for my happy life

357
00:34:58,137 --> 00:34:59,472
(Yukiya) Woohoo...

358
00:35:00,765 --> 00:35:01,599
Umm...

359
00:35:01,682 --> 00:35:03,643
(Erika) After we got married⸺

360
00:35:03,726 --> 00:35:04,644
That kind of thing has completely disappeared.

361
00:35:04,727 --> 00:35:06,896
It's disgusting. Why are you so attached to us?

362
00:35:06,979 --> 00:35:09,357
It was different when you and I lived in that small house.

363
00:35:09,440 --> 00:35:12,276
Maybe you don't like this kind of place?

364
00:35:12,360 --> 00:35:15,571
(Yukiya) Um, um... um...

365
00:35:17,156 --> 00:35:18,282
Um...

366
00:35:18,866 --> 00:35:22,203
(Erika) I want to be happy.

367
00:35:22,286 --> 00:35:25,206
Almost forgetting the painful past

368
00:35:25,289 --> 00:35:28,417
I can pretend it all never happened

369
00:35:28,501 --> 00:35:29,585
I want to be happy

370
00:35:29,669 --> 00:35:31,671
-(Reo) Yukiya-san-(Yukiya) Ah...

371
00:35:32,296 --> 00:35:33,589
Huh...

372
00:35:34,382 --> 00:35:35,675
Huh...

373
00:35:35,758 --> 00:35:38,469
-(Reo) Are you okay? -(Yukiya) Ah...

374
00:35:39,512 --> 00:35:40,763
Yeah

375
00:35:42,932 --> 00:35:44,892
- (Yukiya) Sorry - (Reo) No...

376
00:36:17,425 --> 00:36:18,718
(Nobuo) Ah...

377
00:36:33,357 --> 00:36:34,650
I…

378
00:36:35,985 --> 00:36:37,737
i did it

379
00:36:38,029 --> 00:36:40,031
‪♪～

380
00:36:40,740 --> 00:36:42,950
That child is innocent

381
00:37:09,685 --> 00:37:10,519
Mother...

382
00:37:16,651 --> 00:37:19,528
(Kyoko) Who killed Seiichiro Ise...

383
00:37:20,696 --> 00:37:22,114
Mother!

384
00:37:27,286 --> 00:37:28,913
(Kyoko) It's me.

385
00:37:32,291 --> 00:37:35,836
(Erika) With this, both in name and reality⸺

386
00:37:37,046 --> 00:37:39,548
I became everything about the Ise family.

387
00:37:39,632 --> 00:37:40,716
(shutter sound)

388
00:37:40,800 --> 00:37:42,802
‪～♪

389
00:37:43,135 --> 00:37:45,096
(Photographer) Please look at the center as well.

390
00:37:45,179 --> 00:37:47,056
(shutter sound)

391
00:38:09,412 --> 00:38:11,038
For me at that time...

392
00:38:11,122 --> 00:38:13,124
you were everything

393
00:38:13,207 --> 00:38:14,583
(Erika) I wanted to look back at it.

394
00:38:14,667 --> 00:38:16,168
Fate and everything

395
00:38:16,252 --> 00:38:19,130
You too can quickly become happy⸺

396
00:38:19,213 --> 00:38:21,465
Don't forget about me

397
00:38:21,966 --> 00:38:23,384
Goodbye
